				Ok, as a level 29 Druid on the Tunare server, I can tell you that the info I provide is completely firsthand.  Spirit of Scale is indeed available from both the shaman and the druid spell merchants in Firiona Vie, and the shaman merchant in the Overthere (though what reason a druid would try that is beyond me).  The spell is considerably faster than SOW but will drop under the following conditions: You cast a spell, a spell is cast on you, you attack something, you log.  It does not drop if you are hit melee by something but if you attack back or cast, it's gone.  The best use of this spell is long distance travel that is more convenient running than teleporting.
